title: Oil Price Slips as Market Focuses on Oversupply
text:
Oil dipped on Friday, falling back from the previous sessionâ€™s rally as analysts reminded the market of high U.S. inventory numbers and the continued oversupply of crude.
Brent, the global crude benchmark, was down 1.9% at $47.97 a barrel for cargoes loading in October. Trade in WTI was also down, dropping 2% to $45.01 a barrel on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
